  "name": "Issues Opening Imported Mooks? Read This!",
  "pages": [
    {
      "sort": 100000,
      "name": "Import Individually",
      "type": "text",
      "_id": "jJK2E4zETlNjocjF",
      "title": {
        "show": true,
        "level": 1
      },
      "image": {},
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p>At time of writing (January '24), there is a known issue between Foundry and Foundry RED involving the bulk importation of mooks from compendium packs. If imported as an entire compendium, mook sheets may refuse to open or otherwise lose random bits of functionality. This is, unfortunately, out of my control, but <strong>can easily be circumvented</strong> <strong>by importing mooks </strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><em><strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">individually</span></strong></em></span><strong> from compendiums.</strong> Apologies for the inconvenience, hopefully by the time you're reading this a bug fix will have been issued and this note is no longer relevant.</p>"
      },
